note.p:
Roman numerals in dark ink in the upper right-hand corners of all rectos except for added leaves; the
                                            latter have Roman numerals added in pencil by a modern foliator: 2:173a-2:173d;
                                                2:256a-2:256b.

binding.p:
(?) 17th-century binding consisting of brown leather blind-stamped with decorative frames over pasteboards;
                                    re-backed and the spine gold-stamped with the title inscription: ROGER BACON ON THE ACCIDENTS OF OLD AGE..
                                    Red-speckled fore, head, and tail edges.
